1. PROJECT OVERVIEW
================================================================================

The DTS AI Engine is a Python-based REST API that lets users interact with the Document Tracking
System (DTS) using natural language. Instead of navigating a web portal to look up a document
status, a user can simply type "Where is PDID 001?" and the AI engine will:

  1. Understand the intent of the message (looking for document status)
  2. Extract the document identifier (PDID 001)
  3. Query the DTS backend API for the document's current status
  4. Return a clean, human-readable formatted response
  5. Optionally speak the response aloud in English or Filipino using Text-to-Speech
  6. Remember context across multiple messages in the same conversation session

The system was designed with these major goals:
  - Natural language understanding using a real ML classification model
  - Full integration with the DTS government tracking system
  - Multi-turn conversational memory (sessions)
  - Bilingual support (English and Filipino / Tagalog)
  - Text-to-Speech (TTS) audio output
  - A browser-based web chat UI for easy testing and demonstration
  - Rate limiting to protect all API endpoints from abuse
  - Retrainable ML model — no code changes needed to add new intents


