5. CONFIGURATION SYSTEM (app/config.py)
================================================================================

All configuration is loaded from environment variables using pydantic-settings. The Settings class
inherits from BaseSettings, which automatically reads .env file values at startup.

SETTINGS DEFINED:

  DATABASE_URL          — Full MySQL connection string (default: localhost, root, password)
  DTS_API_BASE_URL      — The base URL of the real DTS API server
  DTS_MOCK_MODE         — Boolean flag (default: True). When True, the app uses built-in sample
                          document data instead of calling the real DTS backend.
  CORS_ORIGINS          — Comma-separated list of allowed CORS origins (default includes
                          localhost:3000 and localhost:5173 for the web app)
  HOST / PORT           — Server binding address (default: 0.0.0.0:8000)
  MODEL_DIR             — Filesystem path where the trained model is saved/loaded
  TRAINING_DATA_DIR     — Filesystem path where CSV training data is stored
  CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD  — Minimum confidence score (0.0 to 1.0) for the classifier to accept
                          a prediction. Below this threshold, the intent is reported as "unknown".
                          Default: 0.4 (40%).

The Settings object is instantiated once at module import time and shared as a singleton across
the entire application via "from app.config import settings".


