16. SECURITY FEATURES
================================================================================

RATE LIMITING (slowapi):
  All mutation endpoints are protected by per-IP rate limits to prevent:
  - Chat flooding: 30/minute limit on /api/chat
  - TTS abuse: 20/minute limit on /api/tts
  - Training spam: 5/minute limit on /api/train (training is computationally expensive)

INPUT VALIDATION (pydantic):
  All request bodies are validated by Pydantic before reaching the handler:
  - Messages must be 1–1000 characters
  - TTS text must be 1–5000 characters
  - Invalid JSON or missing required fields return HTTP 422 automatically

VOICE ALLOWLIST (TTS):
  The /api/tts endpoint only accepts voices from a hard-coded ALLOWED_VOICES set. Any attempt
  to specify an arbitrary voice string returns HTTP 400. This prevents potential abuse of the
  edge-tts library with unexpected voice identifiers.

CORS CONFIGURATION:
  Only origins listed in CORS_ORIGINS (from .env) are allowed to make cross-origin requests.
  Credentials mode is enabled, meaning session cookies (if used in the future) would be handled
  correctly.

ENVIRONMENT-BASED SECRETS:
  Database credentials, API URLs, and CORS origins are never hardcoded — they are always loaded
  from the .env file. The .env file is in .gitignore to prevent credentials from being committed.


