17. DATA FLOW — FULL REQUEST LIFECYCLE
================================================================================

This traces exactly what happens when a user sends "What is the status of PDID 001?" in
a new conversation via the web app:

  1. User types message, selects "English", clicks Send.
  2. main.js freezes the UI, adds user bubble to chat, shows typing indicator.
  3. main.js sends: POST /api/chat
     Body: {"message": "What is the status of PDID 001?", "language": "en"}

  4. FastAPI receives request, Pydantic validates ChatRequest.
  5. Rate limiter checks client IP — within 30/minute limit, proceeds.

  6. process_message() is called:
     a. fetch_admin_documents("What is the status of PDID 001?") — searches DTS API
        for documents matching the keyword. If nothing found, context_string = "".
     b. get_or_create_session(db, None) — no session_id provided, creates new UUID session
        in MySQL sessions table. session.context = {}
     c. classifier.predict("What is the status of PDID 001?"):
        - preprocess_text() → "status pdid 001 ?"
        - TF-IDF vectorizes → numeric vector
        - SGD predicts → "document_status", confidence 0.94
     d. extract_entities("What is the status of PDID 001?"):
        - Pattern 1 matches "PDID 001" → pdid = "001"
        - entities = {"pdid": "001"}
     e. Session context check: context = {}, no pending_intent, no last_pdid.
        intent is "document_status" AND pdid IS in entities → no context change needed.
        last_pdid stored: update_session_context(db, session, "last_pdid", "001")
     f. get_document("001") is called:
        In mock mode: returns the built-in dict for PDID 001 (Juan Dela Cruz leave application)
        In live mode: calls GET {DTS_API_BASE_URL}/api/documents/1, parses result
     g. generate_response("document_status", {"pdid": "001"}, document_data, {}):
        → calls _format_document_status(document_data)
        → builds the full formatted reply text with PDID header, status, location, route history
     h. langdetect.detect(message) → "en", language param = "en" → no translation.
     i. log_message(db, session.id, "user", message, "document_status", 0.94, {"pdid": "001"})
        log_message(db, session.id, "bot", reply)

  7. ChatResponse returned:
     {"reply": "📄 **Document Status for PDID 001**...", "session_id": "abc-uuid", "intent": "document_status", "confidence": 0.94, "entities": {"pdid": "001"}}

  8. main.js receives response, stores session_id for future requests.
  9. Removes typing indicator, adds AI bubble with the reply text.
  10. generateTTS(reply, "en") → POST /api/tts {"text": "...", "voice": "en-US-GuyNeural"}
  11. TTS endpoint:
      - _strip_markdown(text) cleans emojis and formatting
      - langdetect confirms English text → voice stays "en-US-GuyNeural"
      - edge_tts.Communicate(clean_text, "en-US-GuyNeural").stream() generates MP3 chunks
      - StreamingResponse returns MP3 binary
  12. main.js creates Blob URL from MP3, plays via hidden <audio> element.
  13. UI is unfrozen, input is re-enabled and focused.


