23. PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT CONSIDERATIONS
================================================================================

MULTIPLE WORKERS:
  Replace --reload with --workers for production:
    uvicorn app.main:app --workers 4 --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
  Use 2 × CPU_cores + 1 as the worker count. --reload only works with 1 process.

DATABASE CONNECTION POOL:
  Increase pool_size and max_overflow in app/db/database.py to handle concurrent workers:
    pool_size=10, max_overflow=20

DTS RESPONSE CACHE:
  The _document_cache (TTL 60 seconds) is per-process. With 4 workers, each maintains
  its own cache. For shared caching across workers, Redis would need to be added.

RATE LIMITER STORAGE:
  By default, slowapi uses in-memory storage per worker. With multiple workers, rate limits
  are also per-process. For shared rate limiting, configure slowapi to use Redis storage.

SECURITY:
  - Set CORS_ORIGINS to only your production frontend domain
  - Use a strong, random database password
  - Run behind a reverse proxy (nginx) for TLS/HTTPS


